results.question: What does Article 14 guarantee?
results.answer: Article 31C provides that no law giving effect to the policy of the State towards securing all or any of the principles laid down in Part IV shall be deemed void on the ground that it is inconsistent with, or takes away or abridges any of the rights conferred by article 14 or article 19.
